YOLA – The Executive Secretary of the Nígerian Christian Welfare Board Rev Yakubu Pam has challenged Nigerian Christian Politicians to shun corruption and criminal acts so that the country can grow better. Revd Yakubu Pam who gave these charges in Yola, Adamawa State during a stopover at the Yola International Airport said Christians should embrace the sacrifices of the Lord Jesus Christ and shun all vices including corruption and criminalities so that the country can grow.He revealed that much depended on all Christians to show acts of kindness only and to shun stealing and brutal corruption which is rather undermining the nation’s development. He revealed that kindness will produce good fruits which will germinate to successful nationhood but corruption will further collapse the building of a great nation. -Advertisement- He said pilgrimage to Jerusalem for members of the Christian communities in Nigeria would step up after the Covid19 pandemic so that states like Adamawa can effectively participate which is why he came to work out the modality.